name: Answer Man
description: Sit start.

name: No Pitons Here No-Hands
description: Climb the boulder with no hands!

name: Whelmed
description: Start with a left hand high on a decent sidepull and right hand on a crimp.

name: Rainbow
description: Climb up and right on the steep side of the fin. Downclimb on the slabby side.

name: Red Traverse
description: Traverse right, staying below the lip.

name: Bok Choy
description: Start with one had on the undercling.

name: Royal Flush
description: Start deep in the cave.

name: Nasty Boy
description: Climb right side of Bush Craft arete

name: Jump!
description: Hop up to the sloper and mantle.

name: Breadline
description: Climb straight up or go out to the sloper and top out left.

name: Flying Goat Boy
description: Hop up to the sloper and mantle.

name: Bubbles No-Hands
description: Climb the boulder with no hands!

name: Dirty and Deep
description: Climb the low angle right arete.

name: Down the Barrel
description: Optional if the water is low enough - could be a part of the official “Fall” version of the circuit

name: Joel’s Slab
description: Optional if you're up for it!

name: Concavity Stand
description: Start in the crack and climb up and left. Or start on the sidepull left of the crack and climb straight up, eliminating the crack.

name: Sorrow Bird
description: Same start as Lonely Fish.

name: Slice of Pie
description: Optional. Bad landing.

name: Sunny and Steep
description: Climb the left side of the face on rounded jugs. Sit start.

name: Heads Will Roll
description: Optional if the water is low enough.

name: Batman
description: The midday sun can make topping out this one feel a lot harder.

name: Frosting
description: Climb up and right on the left arete.

name: Bad Moon Rising
description: Excellent technical slab with a committing move up high.

name: Lowe Rider Stand
description: Traverse the detached flake, starting from a good left foot.

name: Ice Age Left
description: Climb the left side of the arete - a lot easier than the original.

name: Lonely Fish
description: Use any means necessary to establish on the rail.

name: Power Steering
description: Sit start.

name: Schist Lip
description: Start sitting, rock over at the tree and continue diagonaling up or drop off.

name: Old School
description: This one is tall but the hardest moves are low.

name: Fin Traverse
description: Start on the right side of the fin, shuffle to the left and then pull up to the main boulder, exiting near the top of The Pit.

name: The Rail
description: Sit start. Continue traversing left before topping out for some extra climbing.

name: Squatter Variation
description: Start with a high right hand on the arête and hop a foot up to the pimple.

name: Footless Traverse
description: An option hard and grand ending. Climb in 1 or 2 parts!

name: Rainbow Crack
description: Optional. Climb the easy crack and walk down to Forestland parking.

name: Redneck
description: Short slab.

name: Lead Pants
description: Start sitting.

name: Portal Crack
description: Leads to the top of Moondog and Bad Moon Rising.
